                    1993-



Mr. Myers was the author of more than 900 articles and 
                    five books on the Social Security program. Holds a Guinness 
                    Book of Records world record for testifying before Congress 
                    175 times, during his tenures as Social Security Chief Actuary 
                    from 1947-1970 and as Social Security Deputy Commissioner 
                    from 1981-1982. He was a founding member of the National Academy 
                    of Social Insurance. He was an acknowledged world-class expert 
                    on the Social Security program. Senator Daniel 
                    Patrick Moynihan (D-NY) once described Bob Myers as "a 
                    national treasure." 
