Executive Profile
Robert J. Myers  Chief Executive Officer and President, American Achievement CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships52--
Background

		Mr. Robert J. Myers, also known as Bob, has been Chief Executive Officer and President of American Achievement Corporation since March 14, 2016. Mr. Myers has over 30 years of experience in the merchandise and retail industries, with a focus on sales, marketing, product development and omni-channel distribution strategies. He served as the Chief Executive of Sheplers, Inc. from January 25, 2010 to 2015. He served as the Senior Vice President of Platforms, New Media & ... Broadcast Technology for QVC.com and QVC Inc. He was responsible for setting the online strategic direction for all aspects of QVC.com, QVC''s on- line marketing efforts and its promotional e-mail program. He served as Vice President for Merchandising of QVC.com. Prior to joining QVC, he spent more than 15 years at JCPenney. He served as Merchandise Director of JCPenney and JCP.com since 1999. He serves as a Director at National Retail Federation Inc. He serves as a Member of E-Commerce Advisory Board at DreamIt Ventures. He served as Director of Shop.org. He served as Member of Strategic Advisory Board at Monetate, Inc. from November 17, 2010 to March 13, 2016.Read Full Background




